	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just my 2cp my friend. <br><br>I play a 46 paladin, and I have a range of spells I use during combat. 3 of the spells always in my spell bar are cease (.5 sec stun), desist (1.5 sec stun) and stun (3 sec stun) (the durations might be more or less, but you get the jist of what i'm trying to say, the stuns don't last long). I have these spells in my spell bar for two reasons. The main reason is to stop casters from casting. The second, and more important reason if I'm main tank, is to take aggro. Stun spells take aggro like nothing else, and that is why the stun was included in the proc. A proc (major taunt magnet), a dd (another taunt magnet) and a stun (more tauntage) all in one proc? Can you say &quot;anyother tank try to take aggro from me now?&quot;.<br><br>Quebeldorf<br>46 paladin<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"It is better to reign in Hell than Serve in Heaven"&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>-John Milton<br>Paradise Lost</td></tr>
